    <div class="container-fluid-no faq_wrapper">
        <div class="faq_sections_overlay" itemscope="" itemtype="https://schema.org/FAQPage">
            <section class="faq_section faq_header_section"><h2 class="header__exo">FAQ</h2></section>
            <section itemscope="" itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="faq_section">
                <div data-toggle-for="613bcea3568e2" class="faq_section--head"><h2 itemprop="name"
                                                                                   class="header__subsection">Benefits
                        of getting novavoip</h2>
                    <button class="faq_section--toggle faq_toggle" aria-label="Toggle"></button>
                </div>
                <div id="613bcea3568e2" class="faq_article_overlay" itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                    <article itemprop="text"><p>Unlike other small business phone systems, we're staying on the crest of
                            the technological wave while simultaneously keeping our plans affordable for small business
                            owners.</p></article>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section itemscope="" itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="faq_section">
                <div data-toggle-for="613bcea3568e6" class="faq_section--head"><h2 itemprop="name"
                                                                                   class="header__subsection">Can I have
                        a toll-free number?</h2>
                    <button class="faq_section--toggle faq_toggle" aria-label="Toggle"></button>
                </div>
                <div id="613bcea3568e6" class="faq_article_overlay" itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                    <article itemprop="text"><p>Of course! We have both local numbers and toll-free numbers available,
                            and even better, since all our plans come with multiple numbers, you can always get one of
                            each.</p></article>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section itemscope="" itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="faq_section">
                <div data-toggle-for="613bcea3568e7" class="faq_section--head"><h2 itemprop="name"
                                                                                   class="header__subsection">Can I port
                        in my number?</h2>
                    <button class="faq_section--toggle faq_toggle" aria-label="Toggle"></button>
                </div>
                <div id="613bcea3568e7" class="faq_article_overlay" itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                    <article itemprop="text"><p>We offer porting for numbers going both in and out. So, if your business
                            is well-known, you can take the number with you when you start novavoip for free.</p>
                    </article>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section itemscope="" itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="faq_section">
                <div data-toggle-for="613bcea3568e8" class="faq_section--head"><h2 itemprop="name"
                                                                                   class="header__subsection">What kind
                        of support will I get during set-up?</h2>
                    <button class="faq_section--toggle faq_toggle" aria-label="Toggle"></button>
                </div>
                <div id="613bcea3568e8" class="faq_article_overlay" itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                    <article itemprop="text"><p>We’ll email you detailed instructions on how to set up (it’s only a few
                            steps and can be done in less than 5 minutes).</p>
                        <p>If you do get stuck however, you can either call us or we will call you if we see you’ve been
                            having trouble after a few days.</p></article>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section itemscope="" itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="faq_section">
                <div data-toggle-for="613bcea3568e9" class="faq_section--head"><h2 itemprop="name"
                                                                                   class="header__subsection">What does
                        mini-CRM functionality mean?</h2>
                    <button class="faq_section--toggle faq_toggle" aria-label="Toggle"></button>
                </div>
                <div id="613bcea3568e9" class="faq_article_overlay" itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                    <article itemprop="text"><p>CRM stands for ‘customer relationship manager’ and is software that
                            helps you do just that. While novavoip is still VoIP at its core, recent upgrades to the
                            service to introduce better contact list management and a note-taking system have expanded
                            our services scope into the realm of a CRM-lite.</p></article>
                </div>
            </section>
